ce:section.ce:para:
In addition, PL spectrum analysis has explored the separation and recombination trend of photogenerated electron-hole pairs of the composite materials g-C3N4@CNT and g-C3N4 (
                           Fig. S1
                        ). The PL intensity is designated as the radiative recombination of light-induced charges (Xu et al., 2014). The lower the fluorescence intensity, the higher the separation rate of electrons and holes. It is observed that the peak intensity of the g-C3N4@CNT composite material is significantly lower than that of the single material g-C3N4, indicating that the photogenerated electron-hole pair recombination rate of the g-C3N4@CNT composite material is lower, which also shows that g-C3N4 has sufficient combination with CNT, CNT acts as an electron acceptor and electron transfer body, effectively inhibiting the recombination of electron-hole pairs.
